This paper deals with the problem of classifying tables on the web, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and data management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the organization, representation, storage, and retrieval of information. The paper also uses techniques from natural language processing and machine learning, which are covered in cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) respectively. Additionally, the paper deals with data management, which is covered in cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper uses vector embeddings, which are covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
